sentences: Titus Hjelm (born 15 October 1974) is an academic and musician from Helsinki, Finland.

Previously he was a Reader in Sociology and a lecturer of Finnish Society and Culture at the School of Slavonic and East European Studies, a part of University College London (UCL), where he teaches culture, social science, and literature courses.
Hjelm currently plays bass guitar in the Finnish power metal band
Previously, he played with the Incredible Brainshells and thrash metal band Antidote.
Hjelm entered the Eurovision Song Contest as a part of Thunderstone in 2007 with the song "Forevermore."
The band came second in the Finnish pre-selection final "Euroviisut" of that year.
